      <!-- ═══ USAGE TAB ═══ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">

        <hr style="border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--prism-border); margin: 0 0 40px 0; display: none;" />

        <!-- When and Where to Use -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When and Where to Use</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">The Status Indicator communicates system or record state at a glance using color and text.</p>

          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 24px;">
            <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
              <h3 id="when-to-use-details" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                When to use
              </h3>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Record status in tables (e.g., Active, Inactive, Pending).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Connection or availability status (e.g., Online, Offline).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Workflow state indicators (e.g., Draft, Published, Archived).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">System health in dashboards (e.g., Healthy, Degraded, Down).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">Process status in lists (e.g., Running, Paused, Complete).</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
              <h3 id="when-not-to-use" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
                When NOT to use
              </h3>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For numeric counts -- use Counter instead.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">For category labels -- use Badge or Tag instead.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">For non-interactive decoration without a label.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Semantic States -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="semantic-states" class="doc-section-title">Semantic States</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Each status carries a specific semantic meaning. Use them consistently across your application.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Neutral:</strong> Inactive, idle, unknown -- used when status is indeterminate or not yet set.</li>
            <li><strong>Success:</strong> Healthy, online, completed -- positive states indicating normal operation.</li>
            <li><strong>Warning:</strong> Degraded, at-risk, attention needed -- caution states that may require intervention.</li>
            <li><strong>Critical:</strong> Error, offline, failed, urgent -- negative states requiring immediate attention.</li>
            <li><strong>Info:</strong> Informational, in-progress, active -- neutral-positive states for ongoing operations.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Complete Do's and Don'ts -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Visual and interaction guidelines to ensure Status Indicators are effective and accessible.</p>
          <div class="do-dont-grid">
            <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Consistent mapping:</strong> Use the same status-to-color mapping throughout the entire application.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Include labels:</strong> Always include a text label when the meaning isn't obvious from context.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Dense layouts:</strong> Use Small size for data tables and lists where space is limited.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Semantic consistency:</strong> Neutral=idle, Success=online, Warning=degraded, Critical=error, Info=informational.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Too many types:</strong> Don't use more than 5 status types in a single view.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Color-only:</strong> Don't rely solely on dot color -- always include a label for accessibility.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Wrong component:</strong> Don't use for numeric counts (use Counter) or categories (use Badge/Tag).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Inconsistent sizing:</strong> Don't mix sizes within the same table column or list.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Related -->
        <div class="doc-section">
