        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Typography Tokens -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="typography-tokens" class="doc-h3">Typography Tokens</h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Size</th><th>Token</th><th>Font Size</th><th>Line Height</th><th>Weight</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Small</td><td><code>body/XSmall/Medium</code></td><td>10px</td><td>14px</td><td>500</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Medium</td><td><code>body/Small/Medium</code></td><td>12px</td><td>16px</td><td>500</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Large</td><td><code>body/Default/Medium</code></td><td>14px</td><td>20px</td><td>500</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Layout -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="layout" class="doc-h3">Layout</h3>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">The Status Indicator uses a simple horizontal auto-layout container.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Layout:</strong> Horizontal auto-layout</li>
            <li><strong>Alignment:</strong> Center vertical alignment</li>
            <li><strong>Sizing:</strong> Hugs content (width and height)</li>
            <li><strong>Corner Radius:</strong> 6px</li>
            <li><strong>Item Spacing:</strong> 4px gap between dot, icon, and label</li>
            <li><strong>Padding:</strong> 4px on all sides</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ═══ ACCESSIBILITY TAB ═══ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-accessibility" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">
        <h2 id="accessibility" class="doc-section-title">Accessibility</h2>
        <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for ensuring Status Indicators are accessible to all users and assistive technologies.</p>

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="accessibility-guidelines" class="doc-h3">Accessibility Guidelines</h3>
          <table class="size-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Guideline</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Details</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td><strong>Label</strong></td><td>Always show text label</td><td>Always show text label for screen readers. If the label is visually hidden, use <code>aria-label</code> or <code>sr-only</code> class.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Contrast</strong></td><td>WCAG AA compliant</td><td>All dot colors meet WCAG AA contrast requirements against white backgrounds.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Color Independence</strong></td><td>Text label required</td><td>Text label communicates meaning -- the dot color is supplementary, not the sole indicator.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Screen Reader</strong></td><td>Announced as label text</td><td>The status is announced as its label text (e.g., "Online", "Offline"). Add <code>role="status"</code> for live updates.</td></tr>
              <tr><td><strong>Keyboard</strong></td><td>Focusable if interactive</td><td>If the Status Indicator is interactive, it must be focusable via Tab with a visible focus ring.</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="color-contrast" class="doc-h3">Color Contrast<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(34,197,94,0.15); color: #16a34a;">WCAG AA Pass</span></h3>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">All status dot colors have been verified to meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA contrast requirements.</p>
          <div style="margin-top: 24px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(34,197,94,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(34,197,94,0.2); border-radius: 12px; display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: flex-start;">
             <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#16a34a" stroke-width="2" style="flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px;"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="M12 16v-4"></path><path d="M12 8h.01"></path></svg>
             <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;"><strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA:</strong> All five dot colors (Neutral #5F6C89, Success #0C8844, Warning #E65100, Critical #C1181B, Info #2C66DD) meet the minimum 3.0:1 contrast ratio for UI components against white backgrounds. Text labels use #2A303D which exceeds the 4.5:1 requirement for normal text.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="best-practices" class="doc-h3">Best Practices</h3>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li>Never rely solely on color to communicate status -- always pair with a text label.</li>
            <li>Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">role="status"</code> and <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-live="polite"</code> for status indicators that update dynamically.</li>
            <li>If the indicator is inside a table cell, ensure the cell has an accessible header describing the column purpose.</li>
            <li>For icon-only variants (Show Label = false), always provide an <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-label</code> with the status text.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      </div> <!-- close main-content-inner -->


